Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.59,0:00:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"June 19."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.72,0:00:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,"My first meeting with Franz Bonaparta."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.48,0:00:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"RF179. A very quiet man."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"Refined manner. Wears a suit."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.86,0:00:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,"Children assemble\Nfor book readings in the afternoon."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.50,0:00:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you want to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.42,0:00:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,-To the border.\N-Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.96,0:00:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Czech border.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.17,0:00:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Get in.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.59,0:00:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.31,0:01:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Children assemble\Nfor book readings in the afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.06,0:01:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A very eerie mansion. Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.11,0:01:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,P. Břevnov W.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.61,0:01:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Steeple to the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.53,0:01:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Weather vane to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.37,0:01:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Human dignity. Experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.91,0:01:18.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Magnificent experiments.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.21,0:01:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Depravation of dignity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.79,0:01:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.46,0:01:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, what country are you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.38,0:01:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.38,0:01:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if Japanese people like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.39,0:01:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.64,0:01:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's left over from my lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.68,0:01:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,-Thank you, but--\N-Eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.14,0:01:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like you're about to collapse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.06,0:01:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My wife keeps nagging me to go on a diet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.15,0:01:49.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.07,0:01:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on. Eat up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.74,0:01:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll never make it through\Na long journey if you don't eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.87,0:02:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to bring this journey to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.34,0:03:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.88,0:03:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You let him go? You let Tenma leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.89,0:03:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,-Yes.\N-Why didn't you stop him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.48,0:03:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you know\Nhe's not someone who can be stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.52,0:03:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.61,0:03:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, with Eva Heinemann missing,\Nwe're in a dire situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.82,0:03:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma escaped to save her.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.58,0:04:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That lawyer who called himself Baul,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.75,0:04:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm pretty sure he's the same man\Nwho tried to take my life at my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.59,0:04:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He got close to me\Nto get his hands on my father's notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.22,0:04:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That notebook\Nmust be pretty darn important.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.68,0:04:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.18,0:04:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.77,0:04:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,To where Tenma's going.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.90,0:04:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean the Red Rose Mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.27,0:04:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.11,0:04:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My father's notebook was\Nfilled with perplexing notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.53,0:04:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think this was in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.11,0:04:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Red rose mansion. P. Břevnov W."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.58,0:04:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"P" stands for "Prague."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.62,0:04:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,"W" stands for "west."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.46,0:04:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To the west of the Prague suburb Břevnov.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.13,0:04:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,From there, you can see a steeple to\Nthe left and a weather vane to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.92,0:04:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.26,0:05:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopefully, we'll find someone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.26,0:05:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,at that mansion who can tell us something\Nthat solves all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.39,0:05:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's doubtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.27,0:05:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.65,0:05:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,"Children assemble\Nfor book readings in the afternoon."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.65,0:05:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That was also in the notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.15,0:05:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Children from\Nthat time could tell us something!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.66,0:05:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.58,0:05:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I criticized you earlier\Nfor not stopping Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.04,0:05:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I'd been in your shoes,\NI probably would've done the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.67,0:05:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.93,0:05:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,THREE FROGS
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.30,0:05:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.51,0:05:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in this neighborhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.39,0:05:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.65,0:05:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.90,0:06:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.24,0:06:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.49,0:06:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you should give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.46,0:06:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time we look, you get lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.96,0:06:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm sure I'll remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.00,0:06:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My brother told me what happened back then
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.13,0:06:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was taken from the Three Frogs,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.72,0:06:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what he passed along the way,\Nand where he was taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.97,0:06:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,After passing the station,\Nhe saw the city on the left
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.44,0:06:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and they traveled alongside\Nthe riverside trolley.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.45,0:06:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn right here--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.57,0:06:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.16,0:06:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping secrets from him is a no-no.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.71,0:06:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.88,0:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.60,0:07:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?\NDo you see anything familiar?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.02,0:07:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.44,0:07:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll never find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.48,0:07:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It happened so long ago,\Nyou'll never remember it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.28,0:07:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.90,0:08:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A weather vane on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.16,0:08:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A church steeple on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.62,0:08:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.73,0:08:42.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.86,0:08:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the place?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.57,0:08:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.24,0:08:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But… I know this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.59,0:09:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.19,0:09:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.04,0:09:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a door emerged\Nfrom inside the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.33,0:10:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.04,0:10:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.92,0:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.73,0:10:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The demon is dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.72,0:11:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.93,0:11:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back, Mr. Lipský.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you get an audience?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.40,0:11:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Nobody watched, as usual.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.73,0:11:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But they're such lovely puppets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.28,0:11:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm making now is even lovelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.04,0:11:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hardly wait to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.91,0:11:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll bring it to you\Nas soon as it's finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.29,0:11:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time for me to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.88,0:11:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At the restaurant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.96,0:11:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I can't make a living\Noff of these puppets.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.84,0:11:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so sorry that I've been\Na burden to you for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.26,0:12:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't mind. Don't let it bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Lipský,\Nthere's something I'd like to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.69,0:12:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.77,0:12:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months ago
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.11,0:12:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,when you found me passed out\Nand took me to the hospital…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.94,0:12:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.61,0:12:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing at that mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.95,0:12:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.99,0:12:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.03,0:12:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.04,0:12:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer me, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.71,0:12:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.83,0:12:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.05,0:12:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When I go to that mansion,\NI get ideas for my creations.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.80,0:12:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure how to put it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.14,0:12:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, something else inspires me more…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.77,0:12:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind.\NAnyway, don't worry about staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.90,0:12:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You can stay here for as long as you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.98,0:13:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,May I come in?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.15,0:13:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.07,0:13:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're well enough to get up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.70,0:13:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.37,0:13:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! This must be\Nwhere the puppets are made.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.79,0:13:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I never get an audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.04,0:13:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of story do you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.21,0:13:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a story about a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.01,0:14:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.55,0:14:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing…Please continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.60,0:14:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A demon looking for a reason\Nto destroy the world goes on a trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.60,0:14:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Along the way, he almost dies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.52,0:14:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But a boy\Nwho happens upon him saves his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.36,0:14:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When the boy finds out\Nwho it was he saved,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.20,0:14:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,he chases after the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.99,0:14:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,His travels end when he finds the demon
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.37,0:14:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who he kills with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.46,0:14:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's pretty interesting,\Nbut nobody's interested in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.38,0:14:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.26,0:14:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's probably what I would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.47,0:14:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.81,0:14:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't let him do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.31,0:14:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.48,0:14:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Any human…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.94,0:15:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,would've saved that demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.19,0:15:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.70,0:15:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he'd like this story.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.20,0:15:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's "he"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.28,0:15:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,These books here…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.87,0:15:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all picture books…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.79,0:15:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by Jakob Vyrobek, Klaus Poppe,\Nand Emil Schebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.25,0:15:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Nameless Monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.38,0:15:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.89,0:15:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote many picture books.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.06,0:15:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Jakob Vyrobek, Klaus Poppe,\Nand Emil Scherbe…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all pen names of the same person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.23,0:15:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A man named Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.40,0:15:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.03,0:15:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,People can become…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.12,0:15:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever they want to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.25,0:15:59.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I wasn't a gifted child,\NI was kicked out of the book readings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.25,0:16:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Book readings?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.84,0:16:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,His book readings\Nwere held at the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.97,0:16:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a student there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.39,0:16:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood\Nwhat he was trying to do there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,"A deal! Let's make a deal!"\Nsaid the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.23,0:16:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"No way! Never!"\Nsaid the man with big eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.24,0:16:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,"Sure, let's make a deal,"\Nsaid the man with a big mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.74,0:16:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The garden of the man\Nwith a big mouth flourished.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.25,0:16:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with big eyes was\Nso incredibly poor and hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.05,0:16:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with a big mouth had\Nincredible fun every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.93,0:16:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,He ate his fill\Nof the fruits of his garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.22,0:16:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But he failed to notice that\Nhis garden had withered away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.31,0:17:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In his garden\Nthat would never blossom again,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.19,0:17:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the man with a big mouth wept and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.53,0:17:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"I never should have made\Na deal with the demon."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.87,0:17:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The man with big eyes was so hungry,\Nthat he felt as if he would die.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.12,0:17:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,As the tears streamed down his cheeks,\Nhe said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.29,0:17:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,"I should have made\Na deal with the demon."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.75,0:17:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,"A deal! Let's make a deal!"\Nsaid the demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.59,0:17:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Man with Big Eyes and the Man\Nwith a Big Mouth by Jakob Vyrobek.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.60,0:17:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Every Friday at 3 p.m.,\Nwe'd gather for the book reading.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.61,0:17:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd sit around him\Nand listen to him as he reads a book.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.49,0:17:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He read in a gentle voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.53,0:17:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A very soothing and gentle voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.83,0:18:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Then after he finished a book,\Nhe would ask us this…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.34,0:18:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"The meaning of this story…"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.84,0:18:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.68,0:18:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.22,0:18:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I understood too,\Nafter reading it multiple times.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.22,0:18:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he'd get another picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.31,0:18:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace by Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.07,0:18:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd say,\N"Okay, how about if I read this next?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.74,0:18:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as if this was my first time here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.08,0:18:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Though it's taken quite a long time…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.34,0:18:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,all of my memories have come together now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.10,0:18:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace is always very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.93,0:19:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so busy playing the horn,\Nhe had no time to look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.23,0:19:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace's horn\Nmade everyone happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.48,0:19:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace is always very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.40,0:19:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so busy scattering magical water\Nthat he had no time to look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.86,0:19:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The magical water created green mountains,\Nripened crops, and made flower gardens.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.12,0:19:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of Peace is always very busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.87,0:19:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He was so busy giving everyone names,\Nthat he had no time to look in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.75,0:19:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is "Otto."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.01,0:19:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is "Hans."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.47,0:19:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is "Thomas."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.22,0:19:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is "Johan."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.31,0:19:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,To thank him, Johan gave the god his hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.31,0:19:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The god was very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.11,0:19:52.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted to see\Nhow he looked with the hat on,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.53,0:19:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so he looked in the mirror\Nfor the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.66,0:20:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what he saw in the mirror was a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.12,0:20:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The demon said,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.04,0:20:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,"You are me. I am you."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.33,0:20:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh dear!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.58,0:20:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"Nobody can live in peace\Nwith a demon like this around!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.05,0:20:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,"Oh dear!"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.30,0:20:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In distress, the god…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.64,0:20:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what he did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.60,0:20:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.31,0:20:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what the god did next?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.15,0:20:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I do know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.90,0:20:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I've finally found you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.12,0:20:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.16,0:20:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.95,0:20:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.29,0:20:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Even you couldn't tell us apart, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.67,0:20:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,She was me and I was her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:20:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You are me and I am you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.63,0:21:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand all of it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.09,0:21:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we came from and where we will go.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.81,0:21:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The weather outside is wonderful, Mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.87,0:21:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will be engulfed in flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.27,0:21:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I do know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.48,0:21:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The god will…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.54,0:22:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,point the gun…
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.12,0:22:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,at his forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.55,0:22:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoot me.
